headline: GE Aerospace Supply Strains Test Strong General Electric Share Performance
summary: GE Aerospace executives are highlighting ongoing supply chain disruptions and geopolitical tensions ahead of the Singapore Airshow. Tariffs and global air freight bottlenecks are affecting the flow of parts for both new aircraft engines and maintenance. The company is working to balance strong demand for engines with the need to keep existing fleets in service. headline: JJG Aero Secures $30 Million in Series B Funding from Norwest
summary: Bengaluru-based aerospace components manufacturer JJG Aero has secured $30 million in Series B funding from Norwest. The capital will be deployed primarily to build and add capacity at its upcoming facility in North Bangalore, drive further vertical integration, and support other strategic initiatives. This round brings the total funding raised to $42 million and includes the $12 million Series A led by CX Partners in April 2024.
